# Kali Linux & Nmap Beginner Practice

## Overview

Today I practiced basic commands in Kali Linux and performed simple network scanning using Nmap.
This repository is a record of my hands-on learning and notes.

## Topics Covered

* Basic Linux terminal commands
* File and directory creation
* Understanding IP addresses
* Local network scanning
* Identifying devices and open ports

## Commands Practiced

### File Commands

```
touch file.txt
mkdir test_folder
ls
cd test_folder
pwd
```

### Network Commands

```
ip a
ifconfig
```

### Nmap Scanning

```
nmap 192.168.1.1
nmap -sS 192.168.1.0/24
nmap -A target_ip
```

## What I Learned

* How devices are discovered on a network
* Basics of ports and services
* How Nmap scanning works
* Importance of ethical and legal usage

## Disclaimer

All scans were performed on my own lab network for educational purposes only.

## Next Learning Goals

* Advanced Nmap scanning
* Wireshark basics
* Networking fundamentals
* Ethical hacking labs

Consistent practice. Building cybersecurity skills step by step.
